                          <note>Quire descriptions: quires 3–7 balanced; quires 1, 2, 8 unbalanced.</note>
                          <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1" n="a">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">2</dim>
                                 <locus from="i" to="ii" facs="001">Fols i–ii</locus>
                                 <note>There is, perhaps, a reinforcement strip that goes around the spine of the protection sheet. A stub at the gutter is visible before <locus target="#i" facs="001">fols. i, </locus>; a folio stub, cut off about 1 cm from the gutter is visible between <locus target="#ii #1" facs="003">ii, 1</locus>.</note>
                              Protection Quire
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q2" n="1">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">10</dim>
                                 <locus from="1" to="10" facs="003">Fols 1–10</locus>
                                 <note>
                                    <locus target="#8 #10" facs="010 012">Fols. 8, 10</locus> seem to be single sheets sewn into the quire.</note>
                              Quire 1:
                              8 added
                              10 added
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q3" n="2">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">9</dim>
                                 <locus from="11" to="19" facs="013">Fols 11–19</locus>
